        "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27316312/is-there-a-java-8-or-which-returns-optional-of-present-value-or-default-provi",
        "last_activity_date": 1417785562,
        "creation_date": 1417783879,
        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Is there a Java 8 .or() which returns Optional of present value or default provided?",
        "body": "<p>Suppose I want to provide default value if input value is null, but want to still process <code>Optional<\/code> type, not target type, like this:<\/p>\n\n<p><code>Optional.of(testedValue == null ? testedValue : \"\" ).map(String::trim)...<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Note that I can't use <code>.or<\/code> because it not returns optional<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 27316312,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "null",
            "functional-programming",
            "java-8",
            "option-type"
        ],
        "score": 2,
        "accepted_answer_id": 27316833,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 2912
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/LR4iW.jpg?s=256",
            "account_id": 1114067,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 1103872,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1103872/marko-topolnik",
            "reputation": 201056,
            "display_name": "Marko Topolnik",
            "accept_rate": 82
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 4,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1417785562,
        "creation_date": 1417785562,
        "body": "<p>You can nest another Optional:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Optional.of(\n  Optional.ofNullable(input).orElse(\"\")\n).map(String::trim);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>which is equivalent to<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Optional.of(\n  Optional.ofNullable(input).orElse(\"\").trim()\n);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>So the benefit would be if you continue with more processing steps which may themselves result in no value.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 27316833,
        "question_id": 27316312
    }],
